name: Get alert
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of an alert object.

name: List alerts
description: Retrieve a list of alert objects.

name: Update alert
description: Update an editable alert property within any integrated solution to keep alert status and assignments in sync across solutions. This method updates any solution that has a record of the referenced alert ID.

name: Delete attachment
description: Delete an attachment from a user calendar event, mail message, or group post.

name: Get attachment
description:
Read the properties, relationships, or raw contents of an attachment, attached to a user event,
message, or post.

name: Delete calendar
description: Delete a calendar other than the default calendar.

name: Get calendar
description:
Get the properties and relationships of a calendar object. The calendar can be one for a user,
or the default calendar of an Office 365 group.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: calendar: getSchedule
description: Get the free/busy availability information for a collection of users, distributions lists, or resources (rooms or equipment) for a specified time period.

name: List calendarView
description:
Get the occurrences, exceptions, and single instances of events in a calendar view defined by a time range,
from a user's default calendar (../me/calendarview) or some other calendar of the user's.

name: List events
description: Retrieve a list of events in a calendar.  The calendar can be one for a user, or the default calendar of an Office 365 group. The list of events contains single instance meetings and series masters.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Create event
description: Use this API to create a new event in a calendar. The calendar can be one for a user, or the default calendar of an Office 365 group.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Update calendar
description:
Update the properties of a calendar object. The calendar can be one for a user,
or the default calendar of an Office 365 group.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Delete calendarGroup
description: Delete a calendar group other than the default calendar group.

name: Get calendarGroup
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a calendar group object.

name: List calendars
description: Retrieve a list of calendars belonging to a calendar group.

name: Create Calendar
description: Use this API to create a new calendar in a calendar group for a user.

name: Update calendargroup
description: Update the properties of calendargroup object.

name: Delete channel
description: Delete the channel.

name: Get channel
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a channel.

name: List channels
description: Retrieve the list of channels in this team.

name: Patch channel
description: Update the properties of the specified channel.

name: Create Channel
description: Create a new channel in a Microsoft Team, as specified in the request body.

name: Chart: delete
description: Deletes the chart object.

name: Get Chart
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of chart object.

name: Chart: Image
description: Renders the chart as a base64-encoded image by scaling the chart to fit the specified dimensions.

name: List ChartCollection
description: Retrieve a list of chart objects.

name: Chart: setData
description: Resets the source data for the chart.

name: Chart: setPosition
description: Positions the chart relative to cells on the worksheet.

name: Update chart
description: Update the properties of chart object.

name: ChartCollection: add
description: Creates a new chart.

name: Delete contact
description: Delete a contact.

name: contact: delta
description: Get a set of contacts that have been added, deleted, or updated in a specified folder.

name: Get contact
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a contact object.

name: Update contact
description: Update the properties of a contact object.

name: Delete contactFolder
description: Delete contactFolder other than the default contactFolder.

name: contactFolder: delta
description: Get a set of contact folders that have been added, deleted, or removed from the user's mailbox.

name: Get contactFolder
description: Get a contact folder by using the contact folder ID.

name: List childFolders
description: Get a collection of child folders under the specified contact folder.

name: List contacts
description: Get a contact collection from the default Contacts folder of the signed-in user (.../me/contacts), or from the specified contact folder.

name: Create ContactFolder
description: Create a new contactFolder as a child of a specified folder.

name: Create contact
description: Add a contact to the root Contacts folder or to the contacts endpoint of another contact folder.

name: Update contactfolder
description: Update the properties of contactfolder object.

name: Get Contract
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of contract object.

name: List contracts
description: Retrieve a list of contract objects associated to a partner tenant.

name: List threads
description: Get all the threads in a group conversation.

name: Create thread
description: Create a new thread in the specified conversation.

name: List posts
description:
Get the posts of the specified thread. You can specify both the parent conversation and the thread, or,
you can specify the thread without referencing the parent conversation.

name: conversationThread: reply
description:
Reply to a thread in a group conversation and add a new post to it. You can specify the parent conversation
in the request, or, you can specify just the thread without the parent conversation.

name: Get dataPolicyOperation
description: Retrieve the properties of a dataPolicyOperation object.

name: Delete device
description: Delete a registered device.

name: Get device
description: Get the properties and relationships of a device object.

name: List devices
description: Retrieve a list of device objects registered in the organization.

name: List device groups
description: Get groups that this device is a direct member of. This operation is not transitive.

name: List registeredOwners
description: Retrieve a list of users that are registered owners of the device. A registered owner is the user that cloud joined the device or registered their personal device. The registered owner is set at the time of registration. Currently, there can be only one owner.

name: List registeredUsers
description: Retrieve a list of users that are registered users of the device.

name: List device transitive groups
description: Get groups that the device is a member of. This API request is transitive, and will also return all groups the device is a nested member of.

name: Create device
description: Create and register a new device in the organization.

name: Create registeredOwner
description: Add a user as a registered owner of the device.

name: Create registeredUser
description: Add a registered user for the device.

name: Update device
description: Update the properties of a registered device.

name: Permanently delete item
description: Permanently deletes an item from deleted items.

name: Get deleted item
description: Retrieve the properties of a recently deleted item in deleted items.

name: List deleted items
description: Retrieve a list of recently deleted items from deleted items.

name: Restore deleted item
description: Restores a recently deleted item from deleted items.

name: List deleted items owned by a user
description: Retrieves a list of recently deleted items owned by the specified user.

name: Get directoryAudit
description: Get a specific Azure Active Directory audit log item. This includes an audit log item generated by various services within Azure Active Directory like user, application, device and group management, privileged identity management (PIM), access reviews, terms of use, identity protection, password management (self-service and admin password resets), self-service group management, and so on.

name: List directoryAudits
description: Get the list of audit logs generated by Azure Active Directory. This includes audit logs generated by various services within Azure AD, including user, app, device and group Management, privileged identity management (PIM), access reviews, terms of use, identity protection, password management (self-service and admin password resets), and self- service group management, and so on.

name: Check member groups
description:
Check for membership in a specified list of groups, and returns from that list those groups
of which the specified user, group, or directory object is a member. This function is transitive.

name: Delete directoryObject
description: Deletes a directoryObject.

name: Get directoryObject
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of directoryObject object.

name: Get directory objects from a list of ids
description: Returns the directory objects specified in a list of IDs.

name: Get member groups
description: Return all the groups that the specified user, group, or directory object is a member of. This function is transitive.

name: Get member objects
description: Returns all the groups and directory roles that a user, group, or directory object is a member of. This function is transitive.

name: directoryObject: validateProperties
description: Validate that an Office 365 group's display name or mail nickname complies with naming policies.  Clients can use this API to determine whether a display name or mail nickname is valid before trying to create an Office 365 group. To validate the properties of an existing group, use the group: validateProperties function.

name: Remove directory role member
description: Remove a member from a directoryRole.

name: Get directoryRole
description: Retrieve the properties of a directoryRole object.

name: List directoryRoles
description: List the directory roles that are activated in the tenant.

name: List members
description: Retrieve a list of the users that are assigned to the directory role.  Only users can be assigned to a directory role.

name: Activate directoryRole
description: Activate a directory role. To read a directory role or update its members, it must first be activated in the tenant. Only the Company Administrators and the implicit Users directory roles are activated by default. To access and assign members to another directory role, you must first activate it with its corresponding directory role template (directoryRoleTemplate).

name: Add directory role member
description: Use this API to create a new directory role member.

name: Get directoryRoleTemplate
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a directoryroletemplate object.

name: List directoryRoleTemplates
description: Retrieve a list of directoryRoleTemplate objects.

name: Delete domain
description: Deletes a domain from a tenant.

name: Get domain
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of domain object.

name: List domains
description: Retrieve a list of domain objects.

name: Create domain
description: Adds a domain to the tenant.

name: Update domain
description: Update the properties of domain object.

name: domain: verify
description: Validates the ownership of the domain.

name: Get Drive
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a Drive resource.

name: Get a special folder by name
description: Use the special collection to access a special folder by name.

name: List available drives
description: Retrieve the list of Drive resources available for a target User, Group, or Site.

name: List recent files
description:
List a set of items that have been recently used by the signed in user.
This collection includes items that are in the user's drive as well as items they have access to from other drives.

name: List items shared with the signed-in user
description: Retrieve a collection of DriveItem resources that have been shared with the owner of the Drive.

name: Copy a DriveItem
description: Asynchronously creates a copy of an driveItem (including any children), under a new parent item or with a new name.

name: Create a sharing link for a DriveItem
description: You can use createLink action to share a DriveItem via a sharing link.

name: Upload large files with an upload session
description:
Create an upload session to allow your app to upload files up to the maximum file size.
An upload session allows your app to upload ranges of the file in sequential API requests, which allows the transfer to be resumed if a connection is dropped while the upload is in progress.

name: Delete a DriveItem
description:
Delete a DriveItem by using its ID or path.
Note that deleting items using this method will move the items to the recycle bin instead of permanently deleting the item.

name: Track changes for a Drive
description: This method allows your app to track changes to a drive and its children over time.

name: Get a DriveItem resource
description: Retrieve the metadata for a DriveItem in a Drive by file system path or ID.

name: Download the contents of a DriveItem
description: Download the contents of the primary stream (file) of a DriveItem. Only driveItems with the file property can be downloaded.

name: Download a file in another format
description:
Use this API to retrieve the contents of an item in a specific format.
Not all files can be converted into all formats.

name: Send a sharing invitation
description:
Sends a sharing invitation for a DriveItem.
A sharing invitation provides permissions to the recipients and optionally sends them an email with a sharing link.

name: List children of a driveItem
description: Return a collection of DriveItems in the children relationship of a DriveItem.

name: List sharing permissions on a DriveItem
description: List the effective sharing permissions of on a DriveItem.

name: List thumbnails for a DriveItem
description: Retrieve a collection of ThumbnailSet resources for a DriveItem resource.

name: Listing versions of a DriveItem
description:
OneDrive and SharePoint can be configured to retain the history for files.
Depending on the service and configuration, a new version can be created for each edit, each time the file is saved, manually, or never.

name: Move a DriveItem to a new folder
description: To move a DriveItem to a new parent item, your app requests to update the parentReference of the DriveItem to move.

name: Create a new folder in a drive
description: Create a new folder or DriveItem in a Drive with a specified parent item or path.

name: driveItem: preview
description: This action allows you to obtain short-lived embeddable URLs for an item in order to render a temporary preview.

name: Upload or replace the contents of a DriveItem
description:
The simple upload API allows you to provide the contents of a new file or update the contents of an existing file in a single API call.
This method only supports files up to 4MB in size.

name: Search for a DriveItems within a drive
description:
Search the hierarchy of items for items matching a query.
You can search within a folder hierarchy, a whole drive, or files shared with the current user.

name: Update DriveItem properties
description: Update the metadata for a DriveItem by ID or path.

name: Delete educationClass
description: Delete a class. Because a class is also a universal group, deleting a class deletes the group.

name: Remove a student
description: Removes an educationUser from an educationClass

name: Remove teacher
description: Remove a teacher from a class.

name: Get educationClass
description: Retrieve a class from the system. A class is a universal group with a special property that indicates to the system that the group is a class. Group members represent the students;  group admins represent the teachers in the class. If you're using the delegated token, the user will only see classes in which they are members.

name: List members
description: Retrieves the teachers and students for a class. Note that if the delegated token is used, members can only be seen by other members of the class.

name: List schools
description: Retrieve a list of schools in which the class is taught.

name: List teachers
description: Retrieve a list teachers for a class. Delegated tokens must be members of the class to get the teacher list.

name: Add a student
description: Add a member to a class.

name: Add teacher
description: Add a teacher to a class.

name: Update educationclass properties
description: Update the properties of a class.

name: List classes
description: Retrieve a list of all class objects.

name: List educationSchools
description: Retrieve a list of all school objects.

name: Create educationClass
description:
Create a new class. This will also create a universal group. When you use this API to create a class, it will add special properties to the group, which will
add features such as assignments and special handling within Microsoft Teams.

name: Create educationSchool
description: Create a school.

name: Delete educationSchool
description: Delete a school.

name: Remove educationClass
description: Delete a class from a school.

name: Remove educationUser from an educationSchool
description: Delete a user from a school.

name: Get educationSchool
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of the school object.

name: List educationClasses
description: Retrieve a list of classes owned by a school.

name: List educationUsers
description: Retrieve a list of users at a school.

name: Add educationClass to educationSchool
description: Add a class to a school.

name: Add educationUser to an educationSchool
description: Add a user to a school.

name: Update educationschool properties
description: Update the properties of a school object.

name: Delete educationUser
description: Delete a user.

name: Get educationUser
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a user.

name: List classes
description: Retrieve a list of class objects. Note that if the delegated token is used, members can only see information about their own classes.

name: List schools
description: Retrieve a list of schools for a user.

name: event: accept
description: Accept the specified event in a user calendar.

name: event: decline
description: Decline invitation to the specified event in a user calendar.

name: Delete event
description: Delete event.

name: event: delta
description:
Get a set of events that have been added, deleted, or updated in a calendarView (a range of events)
of the user's primary calendar.

name: event: dismissReminder
description: Dismiss a reminder that has been triggered for an event in a user calendar.

name: Get event
description: Get the properties and relationships of the specified event object.

name: List attachments
description: Retrieve a list of attachment objects attached to an event.

name: List instances
description: Get the instances (occurrences) of an event for a specified time range.

name: Add attachment
description:
Use this API to add an attachment to an event. Since there
is currently a limit of 4MB on the total size of each REST request, this limits the size of the attachment
you can add to under 4MB.

name: event: snoozeReminder
description: Postpone a reminder for an event in a user calendar until a new time.

name: event: tentativelyAccept
description: Tentatively accept the specified event in a user calendar.

name: Update event
description: Update the properties of the event object.

name: Delete eventMessage
description: Delete eventMessage.

name: Get eventMessage
description: Get the properties and relationships of the eventMessage object. Apply the $expand parameter on the event navigation property to get the associated event in an attendee's calendar.

name: List attachments
description: Retrieve a list of attachment objects.

name: Add attachment
description: Use this API to create a new Attachment.

name: Update eventMessage
description: Update the properties of an eventMessage object.

name: group: addFavorite
description: Add the group to the list of the current user's favorite groups. Supported for Office 365 groups only.

name: group: checkMemberGroups
description:
Check for membership in the specified list of groups. Returns from the list those groups of which
the specified group has a direct or transitive membership.

name: Delete group
description: Delete group.

name: Remove acceptedSender
description: Remove a user or group from the accepted-senders list.

name: Delete conversation
description: Delete a conversation object.

name: Delete event
description: Delete an event object.

name: Remove member
description: Use this API to remove a member from a group via the members navigation property.

name: Remove owner
description: Use this API to remove an owner from an Office 365 group, a security group, or a mail-enabled security group through the owners navigation property.

name: Remove rejectedSender
description: Remove a user or group from the rejected-senders list.

name: Delete conversation thread
description: Delete a thread object.

name: group: delta
description: Get newly created, updated, or deleted groups, including group membership changes, without having to perform a full read of the entire group collection. See Using Delta Query for details.

name: Get group
description: Get the properties and relationships of a group object.

name: Get conversation
description: Get a conversation object.

name: Get event
description: Get an event object.

name: Get conversation thread
description: Get a thread object.

name: group: getMemberGroups
description: Return all the groups that the specified group is a member of. The check is transitive, unlike reading the memberOf navigation property, which returns only the groups that the group is a direct member of.

name: group: getMemberObjects
description: Return all of the groups that this group is a member of. The check is transitive. Note: Groups cannot be members of directory roles, so no directory roles will be returned.

name: List groups
description: List all the groups in an organization, including but not limited to Office 365 Groups.

name: List acceptedSenders
description: Get a list of users or groups that are in the accepted-senders list for this group.

name: List calendarView
description:
Get the occurrences, exceptions, and single instances of events in a calendar view defined by a time range,
from the default calendar of a group.

name: List conversations
description: Retrieve the list of conversations in this group.

name: List events
description: Retrieve a list of event objects.

name: List groupLifecyclePolicies
description: Retrieves a list of groupLifecyclePolicy objects to which a group belongs.

name: List memberOf
description: Get groups that the group is a direct member of.

name: List members
description:
Get a list of the group's direct members. A group can have users, contacts, and other groups as members.
This operation is not transitive.

name: List owners
description: Retrieve a list of the group's owners. The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify the group object.

name: List photos
description: Retrieve a list of profilePhoto objects.

name: List rejectedSenders
description: Get a list of users or groups that are in the rejected-senders list for this group.

name: List threads
description: Get all the threads of a group.

name: List group transitive memberOf
description: Get groups that the group is a member of.  This operation is transitive and will also include all groups that this groups is a nested member of. Unlike getting a user's Office 365 Groups, this returns all types of groups, not just Office 365 Groups.

name: List group transitive members
description: Get a list of the group's members. A group can have users, devices and other groups as members. This operation is transitive and will also return a flat list of all nested members.

name: Create acceptedSender
description: Add a new user or group to the acceptedSender list.

name: Create conversation
description: Create a new conversation by including a thread and a post.

name: Create event
description: Use this API to create a new event.

name: Create group
description: Create a new group as specified in the request body. You can create the following types of groups:

name: Add member
description: Add a member to an Office 365 group or a security group through the members navigation property.

name: Add group owner
description: Add a user to the group's owners. The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify the group object.

name: Create rejectedSender
description: Add a new user or group to the rejectedSender list.

name: Create conversation thread
description: Start a new group conversation by first creating a thread.

name: group: removeFavorite
description: Remove the group from the list of the current user's favorite groups. Supported for Office 365 Groups only.

name: group: renew
description: Renews a group's expiration. When a group is renewed, the group expiration is extended by the number of days defined in the policy.

name: group: resetUnseenCount
description: Reset the unseenCount of all the posts that the current user has not seen since their last visit. Supported for Office 365 groups only.

name: group: subscribeByMail
description: Calling this method will enable the current user to receive email notifications for this group, about new posts, events, and files in that group. Supported for Office 365 groups only.

name: group: unsubscribeByMail
description: Calling this method will prevent the current user from receiving email notifications for this group about new posts, events, and files in that group. Supported for Office 365 groups only.

name: Update group
description: Update the properties of a group object.

name: Update event
description: Update an event object.

name: Update conversation thread
description: Update a thread object.

name: group: validateProperties
description: Validate that an Office 365 group's display name or mail nickname complies with naming policies.  Clients can use this API to determine whether a display name or mail nickname is valid before trying to update an Office 365 group. To validate the properties before creating a group, use the directoryobject:validateProperties function.

name: groupLifecyclePolicy: addGroup
description: Adds a group to a lifecycle policy.

name: Delete groupLifecyclePolicy
description: Deletes a groupLifecyclePolicy.

name: Get groupLifecyclePolicy
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of a groupLifecyclePolicies object.

name: List groupLifecyclePolicies
description: List all the groupLifecyclePolicies.

name: Create groupLifecyclePolicy
description: Creates a new groupLifecyclePolicy.

name: groupLifecyclePolicy: removeGroup
description: Removes a group from a lifecycle policy.

name: Update groupLifecyclePolicy
description: Update the properties of a groupLifecyclePolicygroupLifecyclePolicy resource type object.

name: Delete a group setting
description: Delete a group setting.

name: Get a group setting
description: Retrieve the properties of a specific of group setting object.

name: List group settings
description: Retrieve a list of group setting objects.

name: Create a group setting
description: Use this API to create a new setting, based on the templates available in groupSettingTemplates. These settings can be at the tenant-level or at the group level. The creation request must provide settingValues for all the settings defined in the template. For group-specific settings, only the setting governing whether members of a group can invite guest users can be set. This will govern this behavior once the ability to add guest users to a group is generally available.

name: Update a group setting
description: Update the properties of a specific group setting object.

name: Get a group setting template
description: A group setting template represents a template of settings from which settings may be created within a tenant. This operation allows retrieval of the properties of the groupSettingTemplate object, including the available settings and their defaults.

name: List groupSettingTemplates
description: Group setting templates represents a set of templates  from which group settings may be created and used within a tenant.  This operation retrieves the list of available groupSettingTemplates objects.

name: Delete identityProvider
description: Delete an existing identityProvider.

name: Get identityProvider
description: Retrieve the properties of an existing identityProvider.

name: List identityProviders
description: Retrieve all identityProviders in the directory.

name: Create identityProvider
description: Create a new identityProvider by specifying display name, identityProvider type, client ID, and client secret.

name: Update identityProvider
description: Update properties in an existing identityProvider.

name: List overrides
description: Get the overrides that a user has set up to always classify messages from certain senders in specific ways.

name: Create inferenceClassificationOverride
description:
Create an override for a sender identified by an SMTP address. Future messages from that SMTP address will be consistently classified
as specified in the override.

name: Delete inferenceClassificationOverride
description: Delete an override specified by its ID.

name: Update inferenceclassificationoverride
description: Change the classifyAs field of an override as specified.

description: Copy a message to a folder.

description: Create a draft to forward the specified message. You can then update the draft to add content to the body or change other message properties, or, simply send the draft.

name: message: createReply
description: Create a draft of the reply to the specified message. You can then update the draft to add reply content to the body or change other message properties, or, simply send the draft.

description: Create a draft to reply to the sender and all the recipients of the specified message. You can then update the draft to add reply content to the body or change other message properties, or, simply send the draft.

description: Delete a message in the specified user's mailbox, or delete a relationship of the message.

description: Use this API to add an attachment to a message.

name: message: reply
description: Reply to the sender of a message. The message is then saved in the Sent Items folder.

name: message: replyAll
description: Reply to all recipients of a message. The message is then saved in the Sent Items folder.

name: message: send
description:
Send a message in the draft folder. The draft message can be a new message draft, reply draft, reply-all draft, or
a forward draft. The message is then saved in the Sent Items folder.

name: post: forward
description:
Forward a post to a recipient. You can specify both the parent conversation and thread in the request,
or, you can specify just the parent thread without the parent conversation.

name: Get post

Get the properties and relationships of a post in a specified thread. You can specify both the parent
conversation and the thread, or, you can specify the thread without referencing the parent conversation.

description: Retrieve a list of attachment objects attached to a post.

name: Add attachment

name: post: reply

name: Get photo
description: Get the specified profilePhoto or its metadata (profilePhoto properties).

name: Update profilephoto
description:
Update the photo for the signed-in user, or the specified group or contact. Since there
is currently a limit of 4MB on the total size of each REST request, this limits the size of the photo
you can add to under 4MB.

name: Delete an activity
description: Delete an existing user activity for your app.

name: Delete a historyItem
description: Delete an existing history item for an existing user activity.

name: Get user activities
description: Get activities for a given user. Unlike the recent OData function, activities without histories will be returned. The permission UserActivity.ReadWrite.CreatedByApp will apply extra filtering to the response, so that only activities created by your application are returned. This server-side filtering might result in empty pages if the user is particularly active and other applications have created more recent activities. To get your application's activities, use the nextLink property to paginate.

name: Get recent user activities
description: Get recent activities for a given user. This OData function has some default behaviors included to make it operate like a "most recently used" API. The service will query for the most recent historyItems, and then pull those related activities. Activities will be sorted according to the most recent lastModified on the historyItem. This means that activities without historyItems will not be included in the response. The UserActivity.ReadWrite.CreatedByApp permission will also apply extra filtering to the response, so that only activities created by your application are returned. This server-side filtering might result in empty pages if the user is particularly active and other applications have created more recent activities. To get your application's activities, use the nextLink property to paginate.

name: Create or replace an activity
description: Create a new or replace an existing user activity for your app. If you'd like to create a user activity and its related historyItems in one request, you can use deep insert.

name: Create or replace a historyItem
description: Create a new or replace an existing history item for an existing user activity.

name: Range: delete

name: Range: insert

name: Range: merge
description: Merge the range cells into one region in the worksheet.

name: Range: unmerge
description: Unmerge the range cells into separate cells.

name: Update range

name: Update rangeformat

name: reportRoot: getOneDriveUsageAccountDetail

name: reportRoot: getOneDriveUsageFileCounts

name: reportRoot: getOneDriveUsageStorage

name: reportRoot: getSharePointActivityUserDetail

name: reportRoot: getSharePointSiteUsageDetail

name: reportRoot: getSharePointSiteUsageFileCounts
description: Get the total number of files across all sites and the number of active files. A file (user or system) is considered active if it has been saved, synced, modified, or shared within the specified time period.

name: reportRoot: getSharePointSiteUsagePages

name: reportRoot: getSharePointSiteUsageSiteCounts
description: Get the total number of files across all sites and the number of active files. A file (user or system) is considered active if it has been saved, synced, modified, or shared within the specified time period.

name: reportRoot: getSharePointSiteUsageStorage
description: Get the trend of storage allocated and consumed during the reporting period.

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessActivityCounts
description: Get the trends on how many users organized and participated in conference sessions held in your organization through Skype for Business. The report also includes the number of peer-to-peer sessions.

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessActivityUserCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessDeviceUsageUserCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessDeviceUsageUserDetail

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessOrganizerActivityCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessParticipantActivityMinuteCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessParticipantActivityUserCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessPeerToPeerActivityCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessPeerToPeerActivityMinuteCounts

name: reportRoot: getSkypeForBusinessPeerToPeerActivityUserCounts
description: Get usage trends on the number of unique users and type of peer-to-peer sessions held in your organization. Types of sessions include IM, audio, video, application sharing, and file transfers in peer-to-peer sessions.

description: Get the number of Microsoft Teams users by activity type. The activity types are number of teams chat messages, private chat messages, calls, or meetings.

name: reportRoot: getTeamsUserActivityUserDetail
description: Get details about Microsoft Teams user activity by user.

name: reportRoot: getYammerActivityCounts

name: reportRoot: getYammerGroupsActivityGroupCounts

that include extended properties matching a filter.

A site resource represents a team site in SharePoint.

name: Enumerate subsites

msa: Role required to create subscription or Subscription.Read.All (see below).

description: Deletes the table.

name: List columns
description: Retrieve a list of tablecolumn objects.

name: List rows

name: Create TableColumn
description: Use this API to create a new TableColumn.

name: Create TableRow
description: Adds rows to the end of the table. Note that the API can accept multiple rows data using this API. Adding one row at a time could lead to performance degradation. The recommended approach would be to batch the rows together in a single call rather than doing single row insertion. For best results, collect the rows to be inserted on the application side and perform single rows add operation. Experiment with the number of rows to determine the ideal number of rows to use in single API call.

name: Table: Range
description: Gets the range object associated with the entire table.

name: Update table
description: Update the properties of table object.

name: TableCollection: add
description: Create a new table. The range source address determines the worksheet under which the table will be added. If the table cannot be added (e.g., because the address is invalid, or the table would overlap with another table), an error will be thrown.

name: Archive team
description:
Archive the specified team.
When a team is archived, users can no longer send or like messages on any channel in the team, edit the team's name, description, or other settings, or in general make most changes to the team.
Membership changes to the team continue to be allowed.

name: Clone a team
description:
Create a copy of a team. This operation also creates a copy of the corresponding group.
You can specify which parts of the team to clone:

name: Get team
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of the specified team.

name: Create team
description: Create a new team under a group.

name: Unarchive team
description: Restore an archived team. This restores users' ability to send messages and edit the team, abiding by tenant and team settings. Teams are archived using the archive API.

name: Update team
description: Update the properties of the specified team.

name: Remove an app from your organization's app catalog
description:
Remove the app from your organization's app catalog (the tenant app catalog).
To remove your app from your organization's app catalog, specify organization as the distributionMethod in the teamsCatalogApp resource.

name: List the published apps from the Microsoft Teams app catalog
description:
List apps from the Microsoft Teams app catalog.
This includes apps from the Microsoft Teams store, as well as apps from your organization's app catalog (the tenant app catalog). To get apps from your organization's app catalog only, specify Organization as the distributionMethod in the teamsCatalogApp resource.

name: Publish apps to your organization's app catalog
Update apps published to your organization's app catalog
description:
Update an app previously published to the Microsoft Teams app catalog.
This API specifically updates an app published to your organization's app catalog (the tenant app catalog).
To publish to your organization's app catalog, specify organization as the distributionMethod in the teamsCatalogApp resource.

name: Add app to team
description: Install an app to the specified team.

name: Remove app from team
description: Uninstalls an app from the specified team.

name: List apps in team
description: Retrieve the list of apps installed in the specified team.

name: Upgrade an app in a team
description:
Upgrades an app installation in a team
to the latest version of the app.

name: Add tab to channel
description:
Adds (pins) a tab to the specified channel within a team.
The corresponding app must already be installed in the team.

name: Delete tab from channel
description: Removes (unpins) a tab from the specified channel within a team.

name: Get tab
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of the specified tab.

name: List tabs in channel
description: Retrieve the list of tabs in the specified channel within a team.

name: Update tab
description:
Update the properties of the specified tab.
This can be used to configure the content of the tab.

name: assignLicense
description: Add or remove subscriptions for the user. You can also enable and disable specific plans associated with a subscription.

name: checkMemberGroups
description:
Check for membership in the specified list of groups. Returns from the list those groups of which
the user has a direct or transitive membership.

name: Delete a user
description: Delete user.

name: user: delta
description: Get newly created, updated, or deleted users without having to perform a full read of the entire user collection. See Track changes for details.

name: user: exportPersonalData

name: user: findMeetingTimes
description: Suggest meeting times and locations based on organizer and attendee availability, and time or location constraints specified as parameters.

name: Get a user
description: Retrieve the properties and relationships of user object.

name: Get user mailbox settings
description:
Get the user's mailboxSettings. This includes settings for automatic replies (notify people automatically upon
receipt of their email), locale (language and country/region), and time zone, and working hours.

name: Get settings
description:
Read the user and organization settings object.
To learn how to update the properties of the settings object, see update user settings.

name: user: getMailTips
description: Get the MailTips of one or more recipients as available to the signed-in user.

name: user: getMemberGroups
description:
Return all the groups that the user is a member of. The check is transitive, unlike reading the
memberOf navigation property, which returns only the groups that the user is a direct member of.

name: user: getMemberObjects
description: Return all of the groups, directory roles and administrative units that the user is a member of. The check is transitive.

name: List users
description: Retrieve a list of user objects.

name: List calendarGroups
description: Get the user's calendar groups.

name: List calendars
description: Get all the user's calendars (/calendars navigation property), get the calendars from the default calendar group or from a specific calendar group.

name: List calendarView
description:
Get the occurrences, exceptions, and single instances of events in a calendar view defined by a time range, from the user's default calendar,
or from some other calendar of the user's.

name: List contactFolders
description: Get the contact folder collection in the default Contacts folder of the signed-in user.

name: List contacts
description: Get a contact collection from the default contacts folder of the signed-in user.

name: List createdObjects
description: Get a list of directory objects that were created by the user.

name: List directReports
description: Get a user's direct reports.

name: List events
description:
Get a list of event objects in the user's mailbox. The list contains single
instance meetings and series masters.

name: List joinedTeams
description: Get the teams in Microsoft Teams that the user is a direct member of.

name: List mailFolders
description: Get the mail folder collection directly under the root folder of the signed-in user. The returned collection includes any mail search folders directly under the root.

name: List manager
description: Get user's manager. Returns the user or contact assigned as the user's manager.

name: List memberOf
description: Get groups and directory roles that the user is a direct member of.

name: List messages
description: Get the messages in the signed-in user's mailbox (including the Deleted Items and Clutter folders).

name: List ownedDevices
description: Get the list of devices that are owned by the user.

name: List ownedObjects
description: Get the list of directory objects that are owned by the user.

name: List people
description: Retrieve a collection of person objects ordered by their relevance to the user, which is determined by the user's communication and collaboration patterns, and business relationships.

name: List registeredDevices
description: Get the list of user's registered devices.

name: List user transitive memberOf
description: Get groups, directory roles that the user is a member of. This API request is transitive, and will also return all groups the user is a nested member of.

name: Create CalendarGroup
description: Use this API to create a new CalendarGroup.

name: Create Calendar
description: Use this API to create a new calendar for a user.

name: Create ContactFolder
description: Create a new contactFolder under the user's default contacts folder.

name: Create Contact
description: Add a contact to the root Contacts folder or to the contacts endpoint of another contact folder.

name: Create Event
description: Create an event in the user's default calendar or specified calendar.

name: Create MailFolder
description: Use this API to create a new mail folder in the root folder of the user's mailbox.

name: Assign a manager
description: Use this API to assign a user's manager.

name: Create Message
description: Use this API to create a draft of a new message. Drafts can be created in any folder and optionally updated before sending. To save to the Drafts folder, use the /messages shortcut.

name: Create User
description:
Create a new user.
The request body contains the user to create. At a minimum, you must specify the required properties for the user. You can optionally specify any other writable properties.

name: user: reminderView
description: Return a list of event reminders in a user calendar within the specified start and end times.

name: Send mail
description: Send the message specified in the request body. The message is saved in the Sent Items folder by default.

name: user: translateExchangeIds
description: Translate identifiers of Outlook-related resources between formats.

name: Update user
description: Update the properties of a user object.

name: Update user mailbox settings
description: Update one or more settings for the user's mailbox. This includes settings for automatic replies (notify people automatically upon receipt of their email), locale (language and country/region), time zone, and working hours.

name: Update settings
description:
Update the properties of the settings object.
Users in the same organization can have different settings based on their preference or on the organization policies.
To get the user current settings, see current user settings.

This operation is only permitted for an access review that is not yet completed, and only for an access review where the reviewers are explicitly specified. This operation is not permitted for an access review in which users review their own access, and not intended for an access review in which the group owners are assigned as the reviewers.

description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, retrieve an accessReview object.

name: List accessReviews
description: Retrieve the accessReview objects for a particular businessFlowTemplate. A list of zero or more accessReview objects are returned, for each one-time and recurring access review that was created with that business flow template.

name: List accessReview decisions
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, retrieve the decisions of an accessReview object.

name: List my accessReview decisions
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, retrieve the decisions of an accessReview object for the calling user as reviewer.

name: List accessReview reviewers
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, retrieve the reviewers of an accessReview object.

name: Remove accessReview reviewer
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, update an existing accessReview object to remove a user as a reviewer.  This operation is only permitted for an access review that is not yet completed, and only for an access review where the reviewers are explicitly specified. This operation is not permitted for an access review in which users review their own access, and not intended for an access review in which the group owners are assigned as the reviewers.

name: Reset accessReview
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, reset the decisions of a currently active accessReview.  The target object can be either a one-time access review, or an instance of a recurring access review.  Previous decisions are no longer recorded, but reviewers can continue to update decisions.

name: SendReminder accessReview
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, send a reminder to the reviewers of a currently active accessReview.  The target object can be either a one-time access review, or an instance of a recurring access review.

name: Stop accessReview
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, stop a currently active accessReview.  The target object can be either a one-time access review, or an instance of a recurring access review.  (To prevent a recurring access review from starting future instances, update it to change its scheduled end date).  After the access review stops, reviewers can no longer give input, and the access review decisions can be applied.

name: Update accessReview
description: In the Azure AD access reviews feature, update an existing accessReview object to change one or more of its properties.

name: Add educationCategories
description: Add one or more existing educationCategory objects to this educationAssignment.

name: Delete educationAssignment
description: Delete an existing assignment. Only teachers within a class can delete assignments.

name: Remove educationRubric from educationAssignment
description: Remove an educationRubric from an educationAssignment.  This does not delete the rubric itself.

name: Get educationAssignment
description: Get the properties and relationships of an assignment. Students can only see assignments assigned to them; teachers can see all assignments in a class.

name: Get educationRubric attached to educationAssignment
description: Get the educationRubric object attached to an educationAssignment, if one exists.

name: educationAssignment: getResourcesFolderUrl
description:
This function returns the OneDrive URL where all file-based resources (Word, Excel, and so on) should be uploaded.
Note that files must be located in this folder in order to be added as resources. Only a teacher in the class can determine what files to upload.

name: List categories
description: List all the categories associated with this assignment.

name: List educationAssignmentResources
description: Get all the resources associated with this assignment.

name: List submissions
description: List all the submissions associated with this assignment. A teacher can get all the submissions while a student can only get submissions that they are associated with.

name: Create educationAssignmentResource
description: Create an assignment resource. The resource itself has an @odata.type to indicate which type of resource is being created. Note that file-based resources must first be uploaded to the assignments resourceFolder.

name: educationAssignment: publish
description: This action changes the state of an assignment from its original draft status to the published status. Only a teacher in the class can make this call. When an assignment is in draft status, students will not see the assignment, nor will there be any submission objects. When you call this API, submission objects are created and the assignment appears in the student's list.

name: Create educationRubric
description: Attach an existing educationRubric object to an educationAssignment.

name: Remove educationCategory
description: Remove an educationCategory from an educationAssignment.

name: Update educationassignment
description: Update the assignment object. Only teachers in the class can do this. Note that you can't use a PATCH request to change the status of an assignment. Use the publish action to change the assignment status.

name: Delete educationAssignmentResource
description: Delete a resource from an assignment. Only teachers in the class can remove a resource. After an assignment has been published to students, teachers cannot remove resources that are marked as "distributeToStudents".

name: Get educationAssignmentResource
description: Get the properties of a specific resource on an assignment.

name: Update educationAssignmentResource
description: Update the properties of resource associated with an assignment. Only teachers in a class can change assignment resource objects.

name: Delete educationCategory
description: Delete an existing category.

name: Get educationCategory
description: Retrieve an educationCategory object.

name: educationClass: delta
description: Get newly created or updated classes, including membership changes, without having to perform a full read of the entire class collection. See Use delta query for details.

name: List assignments
description: Retrieve a list of assignment objects. A teacher is allowed to see all assignment objects for the class. Students can only see assignments that are assigned to them.

name: List educationCategories
description: Retrieve a list of educationCategory objects.

name: Create educationAssignment
description: Creates a new assignment. Only teachers in a class can create an assignment. Assignments start in the Draft state, which means that students will not see the assignment until publish is called.

name: Create educationCategory
description: Creates a new educationCategory on an educationClass.

description: Retrieve a particular submission. A submission object represents a student's work for an assignment. Resources associated with the submission represent this work. Only the student the submission is assigned to can see and modify the submission. A teacher has full access to all submissions.

name: List outcomes
description: Retrieve a list of educationOutcome objects.  There are three types of outcomes: educationPointsOutcome, educationFeedbackOutcome, and educationRubricOutcome.

name: List resources
description: List the resources associated with this submission. The submissionResource object is a wrapper around the actual resource object the student is working on. The wrapper also includes a pointer to the resources on the assignment if this was copied from the assignment during the assign process. These resources are the working copy of the assignment. The submittedResources are the resources that have officially been submitted to be graded.

name: List submittedResources
description: List the resources that have officially been submitted for grading. The student who owns the submission cannot change the submitted list without resubmitting the assignment. This is a wrapper around the real resource and can contain a pointer back to the actual assignment resource if this resource was copied from the assignment.

name: Create educationSubmissionResource
description: Adds a resource to the resources list. This action can only be done by the student to whom this submission is assigned. This action will not succeed if the allowStudentsToAddResources flag is not set to true. If the caller wants to create a new file-based resource, the file must be uploaded to the resources folder that is associated with the submission. If the file does not exist or is not in that folder, the POST request will fail.

name: educationSubmission: return
description: This action makes the grade and feedback associated with this submission available to the student. This will change the status of the submission from "submitted" to "returned" and indicates that feedback is provided or grading is done. This action can only be done by the teacher.

name: educationSubmission: submit
description: An action that indicates that a student is done with the work and is ready to hand in the assignment. This action can only be taken by the student. This will change the status of the submission from "working" to "submitted". During the submit process, all the resources will be copied to the submittedResources bucket. The teacher will be looking at the submitted resources list for grading.

name: educationSubmission: unsubmit
description: An action that indicates that a student wants to work on the submission of the assignment after it was turned in. This action can only be taken by the student. This will change the status of the submission from "submitted" to "working". During the submit process, all the resources will be copied from submittedResources to the workingResources bucket. The teacher will be looking at the working resources list for grading.

name: Update educationsubmission
description: Add a grade and feedback to a submission. Only teachers can perform this operation. Note that the Basic permission does not have access to the grade properties, and therefore cannot write to grade or feedback. This action does not release the grade and feedback to the student. A teacher must take an explicit release action for the grade data to be returned to the student.

name: Delete educationSubmissionResource
description: Deletes a resource from the submission. This can only be done by the student. If the resource was copied from the assignment, a new copy of the resource will be created after the current copy is deleted. This allows you to "reset" the resource to its original state. If the resource was not copied from the assignment but was added from the student, the resource is simply deleted.

name: Get educationSubmissionResource
description: Retrieves the properties of a specific resource associated with the submission. This resource is in the "working" resource list and should be considered work in process by a student. This resource is wrapped with a possible pointer back to the assignment resource if it was copied from the assignment.

name: Get educationSubmittedSubmissionResource
description: Returns a submitted resource. This will be available to a teacher after a student has submitted, and will be available to the student after the teacher has released the submission.  Note that teachers can leave notes in some resources.

name: Get educationSynchronizationErrors
description: Get the errors generated during validation and/or during a sync of a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Delete a educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Delete a school data synchronization profile in the tenant based on the identifier.

name: Get an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Retrieve a school data synchronization profile in the tenant based on the identifier.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: List educationSynchronizationProfiles
description: Retrieve the collection of school data synchronization profiles in the tenant.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Pause sync on an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Pause the sync of a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Create an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Create a request for a new school data synchronization profile in the tenant. Query the status to get the status of the profile.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Reset sync on an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Reset the sync of a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Resume sync on an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Resume the sync of a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Start sync after uploading files to an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Verify the files uploaded to a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant. If the verification is successful, synchronization will start on the profile. Otherwise, the response will contain errors and warnings. If the response contains errors, the synchronization will not start. If the response contains only warnings, synchronization will start.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: educationSynchronizationProfile: uploadUrl
description: Retrieve a shared access signature (SAS) for uploading source files to Azure blob storage for a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant. The SAS token has a validity of one hour.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: Get the status of an educationSynchronizationProfile
description: Get the status of a specific school data synchronization profile in the tenant. The response will indicate the status of the sync.
permissions: Need permission for resources. For more details, check document

name: schedule: share
description:
Share a schedule time range with schedule members.
Make the collections of shift and timeOff items in the specified time range of the schedule viewable by the specified team members, including employees and managers.
Each shift and timeOff instance in a schedule supports a draft version and a shared version of the item. The draft version is viewable by only managers, and the shared version is viewable by employees and managers. For each shift and timeOff instance in the specified time range, the share action updates the shared version from the draft version, so that in addition to managers, employees can also view the most current information about the item. The notifyTeam parameter further specifies which employees can view the item.

If you're using LaunchURI, specify the type and payload parameters. For an AppService call, specify the
type, payload, packageFamilyName, and appServiceName parameters.
